2ï¸âƒ£ Importance of Cleaning in Semiconductor Manufacturing

â€œCleaning is one of the most important steps in semiconductor fabrication.

During the process â€” deposition, photolithography, etching, and CMP â€” tiny particles or chemical residues remain on the wafer surface.
If we donâ€™t remove them completely, they can cause defects in the next step and reduce yield.

Thatâ€™s why wet cleaning is repeated many times throughout the entire process. For example:
â€¢ After deposition, we remove film debris and chemical residues.
â€¢ After photolithography, we remove photoresist and organic residues.
â€¢ After etching, we remove metal ions and etch by-products.
â€¢ After CMP, we remove slurry particles and metallic contamination.

So cleaning is not just one step â€” it is repeated many times to keep the wafer surface perfectly clean.â€

